http_ping
------------------------------------------
http_ping is like the regular ping command, except that it sends HTTP requests
instead of ICMP echo requests.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libssl1.1-1.1.1f-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.acme.com/software/http_ping/

Canonical download:
  http://www.acme.com/software/http_ping/http_ping_09Mar2016.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack http_ping-20160309-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./http_ping-20160309-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/http_ping-20160309-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/http_ping-20160309-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(http_ping)
  /usr/bin/http_ping.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/http_ping.README
  /usr/share/doc/http_ping/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/http_ping.1.gz

